cs.CV, cs.GR, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM 

The paper deals with the problem of inferring 3D shapes from 2D images, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The use of generative adversarial networks (GANs) is also a key aspect of the paper, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also involves the use of differentiable projection operators, which are commonly used in computer graphics (cs.GR) and multimedia (cs.MM).
